Nigerian rapper, Jude Abaga, popularly known as M.I, has quit Chocolate City to float new record label, “Incredible Music”, after 13 years of being under the record label. M.I made this announcement in an Instagram post few hours after his 10th studio project, “Judah EP”, an-eight-track project, was released on Friday. Judah EP was released under his new record label, “Incredible Music”. He said, “There is a lot of truth in my new EP the “Judah EP”. I had a dream that CBN would be the greatest group the world had ever seen…it was on me.. and today I announce my decision to finally let go and move on to something new! “Thank you for your support and love for 13 years.. and if your still with me!! Let’s go.. please follow @imthetribe. Signed to Chocolate City in 2008, M.I released four solo albums, three mixtapes and a compilation album and was appointed the CEO of Chocolate City on June 30, 2015.